$interpreted: Chiyuki: Hot Spring Street is just a little further ahead.
Chiyuki: It's customary for the top tournament competitors to take a few nights to themselves at Hot Spring Street, so we hope everyone can enjoy themselves.
Soohyeon: Why's Himawari lagging behind so much? Maybe we should...
Toyokuni: Let her be. After what just happened to her, I think she needs some time to herself.
Pang: Yes, I agree that she needs some alone time.
Soohyeon: What do you think, Tindoiimu?
Tindoiimu: It's her business, not ours.
Soohyeon: Hmm... if that's how everyone feels, then fine...
Soohyeon: ...Eh? It's kind of dead around here. I thought it would be a bit more bustling.
Toyokuni: It used to be, but the Insect Tribe rebels attacked here recently.
Toyokuni: There were Fog Sect troops stationed all around here, too, but the Insect Tribe... it's like they went completely insane.
Toyokuni: In the end, many of the troops and locals perished, and the rest fled. All that's left is what you see here.
Soohyeon: Wow...
Himawari: ...Boring.
Tindoiimu: (...What a scene... of course it could only end in absolute destruction...)
Tindoiimu: (I don't want to see anyone else die... but, I have to admit that the Alliance has pushed us to this point.)
Toyokuni: ...Our tribe tried to convince the Alliance to re-open talks with the Insect Tribe, but it was no use. Now, seeing this... I'm afraid there's no way back.
Tindoiimu: The Komainu Tribe wanted to negotiate!? Why!?
Toyokuni: Why not? My family's been killed by the Insect Tribe, and your family's been killed by the Alliance.
Tindoiimu: ...But you still...
Toyokuni: We've wronged you, and you've wronged us. I can understand your despair.
Tindoiimu: ......
Toyokuni: So, I would think the better thing to do, rather than kill each other, would be to discuss matters and see things from each other's perspective.
Toyokuni: ...In the end, I was one of the few who thought that way. If the Insect Tribe wishes to attack, I have no choice but to retaliate.
Toyokuni: After all, I am part of this Alliance, and part of my tribe. I must act accordingly.
Tindoiimu: ......
Soohyeon: Ah... uh... Are you alright, Tindoiimu? Maybe we should catch up with the others.
Tindoiimu: (See things from... each other's perspective?)
Soohyeon: ...Tindoiimu?
Tindoiimu: (...Is this my fault? Because I've only ever thought of revenge?)
Tindoiimu: (Because I thought that was the only choice? And I completely threw away any other possibilities for peace?)
Tindoiimu: (Was I... wrong?)
Chiyuki: Well, everyone, we're here! The district that never sleeps, Hot Spring Street!
Chiyuki: There's all sorts of hot spring spas here, as well as all kinds of little shops and restaurants~
Guest: You call yourself a business owner!? Then you should know the customer's always right!
Pang: Is someone having an argument?
Chiyuki: Ah, that's one of Hot Spring Street's... guesthouses.
???: Please don't be mad... you'll scare the girls.
Guest: If you don't want me to be mad, then you better do as I say! You're the most popular joint around here, you should know how to run your business!
???: Yes, it's my fault, I'm very sorry! But, we're really just not open right now...
Guest: Meanwhile I'm here trying to give you business! You should be honored by my presence, you know that!?
Guest: What are you, just a bunch of half-rate demihuman trash? Like those damn maggots!? How the heck do you think you'll make it on Hot Spring Street!?
Guest: If you're not open for business, then how 'bout I open you up!?
???: Ow! That hurts...!
Tindoiimu: ...Leave her alone.
Guest: Oh? And who are you stickin' your nose in my business? You got a death wish?
Tindoiimu: You...
Soohyeon: What's wrong, Tindoiimu?
Tindoiimu: ......
Tindoiimu: Nothing.
Soohyeon: Ah! Did you... did you just smile at me?
Tindoiimu: ...No.
Soohyeon: But I swear I just saw you smile—
???: Um, my name is Beyata, and these are some of my co-workers... Thank you so much for saving us...
Tindoiimu: I just didn't like his tone of voice. I wasn't doing it for you.
???: You're very humble, Princess, but I still must thank you for helping me and my girls...
Chiyuki: Ah, but you're... Izumi!?
Izumi: Ah, it's been a long time, Chiyuki~
Izumi: I've been in front of the guesthouse here all day and haven't seen a soul. I thought you'd gotten lost~
Chiyuki: I'm sorry we didn't arrive on time. We ran into some bumps in the road...
Izumi: I saw~ Thanks again, you saved me from having to step in.
Toyokuni: Miss Chiyuki, who is this?
Chiyuki: Everyone, this is Izumi. He owns quite a lot of the establishments here on Hot Spring Street.
Chiyuki: And he also owns the guesthouse you're all staying at.
Pang: Weren't you on the same boat as me while coming over? You're from the Desert Kingdom, right?
Izumi: Ah, the tiger from the ship! What a small world~
Izumi: Now, just to let everyone know, there are some special rules here on Hot Spring Street.
Izumi: Beyata, please go and find that guest from just now see if you can get a smile back on his face~
Beyata: Of course, Izumi, I'll be sure to make him happy~
Izumi: Now, welcome to Hot Spring Street! Make yourselves at home! Eat well and be merry!
Izumi: Actually, would anyone be interested in taking a peek inside our very own Red Palace? It would be quite the rare treat!
Izumi: Our matchmaker is one of the most famous in all the east!
Pang: M-Matchmaker?
Izumi: We're here~
Soohyeon: What a pretty gate~
Tindoiimu: ...I'm a hostage, so it's no wonder I haven't been here, but... Soohyeon, you haven't been here before either?
Soohyeon: My mom is quite protective over me... she doesn't like me running around.
Tindoiimu: ...What about that Yonghyeon? He could always go with you.
Soohyeon: Yonghyeon doesn't like hot springs. I've asked him a million times, he always says no.
Merchant: The Red Palace has all sorts of wonderful charms for sale! Would you like to fall in love? Or maybe get married? Maybe have children!?
Merchant: Charms, necklaces, rings... we've got it all!
Single Lady: Wow, this blue-green charm looks beautiful. Should I buy it?
Soohyeon: Charm...?
Izumi: Yep. Most of the products here ar made by demihumans, especially the charms.
Izumi: Apparently whoever started making these learned from the Rune Academy, over in the Kingdom of the Sun. So the style isn't very 'eastern'.
Izumi: Actually, that decoration on your skirt looks a bit similar.
Soohyeon: (Oh yeah, Li Hwa made this charm, and she studied at the Rune Academy, too...)
Tindoiimu: So your charm is meant for finding love, too?
Soohyeon: Eh!? No!
Tindoiimu: Then what's it for...?
Soohyeon: Uh... it's... uhhhh...
Soohyeon: (I can't tell them what it's actually for...)
Soohyeon: It's not for finding love, it's... it's actually kind of an anti-love charm!
Tindoiimu: ......
Soohyeon: Um, I mean... think about it, Tindoiimu...
Soohyeon: Juan-Yun has always been a kind of flirty guy with everyone, hasn't he?
Tindoiimu: ……………
Soohyeon: I've always wanted him to stop all that... I've tried almost every kind of love curse out there, so I thought...
Soohyeon: Maybe I should try one of these anti-love charms that the humans make, you know?
Tindoiimu: Uh-huh... You two are getting married, so it makes sense.
Soohyeon: ...Tindoiimu? What's wrong? Did I say something to upset you?

Tindoiimu: No, I'm fine...
I wish you both the best.
